cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper discusses regularization techniques for deep learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel regularization technique that is directly applied to the weights of the CNNs, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
